Definition: a person authorized to conduct religious worship
Example: clergymen are usually called ministers in Protestant churches
Synonyms: minister_of_religion, minister, adj, pert, ministerial, verb, social, parson, pastor, pastoral, noun, act, pastorship, rector, clergyman, a, person, authorized, to, conduct, religious, worship, clergymen, are, usually, called, ministers, in, Protestant, churches
Category: noun.person
